Wataƙila, an riga an daidaita shi zuwa wani mai masaukin da ke kusa da mutane.
Baya ga SARS-CoV-2, wannan kuma ya shafi MERS-CoV, wanda ya dace da raƙuman dromedary.
A ka'ida, ba shi yiwuwa cewa jujjuyawar kwayoyin halitta za ta sa alluran rigakafi da magungunan rigakafin cutar SARS-CoV-2 su zama marasa tasiri da sauri.
Na biyu, babban kwayar RNA a cikin CoVs yana da ƙarin filastik a cikin gyaran kwayar halitta don sauyawa da sake haɗawa, don haka yana ƙara yiwuwar juyin halitta tsakanin jinsuna, wanda ke da fa'ida don fitowar sabbin CoVs lokacin da yanayi ya dace.
Wannan yana tallafawa ta hanyar manyan takamaiman buɗe ɗakunan karatu da ayyukan furotin da aka tsara zuwa ƙarshen 3 'na kwayoyin halitta.
Na uku, CoVs suna canza samfuran bazuwar kuma sau da yawa yayin kwafin RNA ta hanyar tsari na musamman na copy-choice.
A cikin mai masaukin da ke aiki a matsayin kwandon haɗuwa, sauya zaren yana faruwa sau da yawa yayin kwafin RNA na CoV.
RNAs masu cikakken tsawon da subgenomic masu kama da juna na iya sake haɗuwa don samar da sabbin CoVs.
An sami shaidar phylogenetic na sake haɗuwa ta halitta a cikin HCoV-HKU1 da HCoV-OC43, da kuma CoVs na dabbobi kamar su bat SL-CoV da batCoV-HKU9.
Haɗin kai tsakanin kwayar cutar da mai masaukin a dangane da watsawa
Baya ga abubuwan da aka ambata a sama guda uku, hulɗar kwayar cuta da mai karɓar mai watsawa wani muhimmin abu ne wanda ke tasiri kan watsawar tsakanin jinsuna.
A nan, ana ɗaukar sake haɗuwa da SARS-CoV a matsayin misali na yau da kullun, wanda kuma ya nuna shaidar zaɓi mai kyau yayin abubuwan watsawa tsakanin nau'ikan.
Dangane da kwatancen bincike tsakanin keɓaɓɓun mutane da civet SARS-CoVs, ana tsammanin SARS-CoV yana fuskantar saurin daidaitawa a cikin runduna daban-daban, musamman tare da sauye-sauye a RBD na furotin S.
Gabaɗaya, RBD a cikin furotin S na CoV yana hulɗa tare da mai karɓar ƙwayoyin cuta kuma ana zaɓar shi sosai ta hanyar amsawar kwayar cutar mai masaukin baki.
A cikin SARS-CoV, RBD yana cikin amino acid na 318 zuwa 510 akan ɓangaren S1, wanda ke ɗaure ga ACE2 na ɗan adam da kuma masu karɓar ƙwayar cuta don shigar da kwayar cuta.
RBD na SARS-CoV yana iya gane masu karɓar ACE2 na dabbobi daban-daban, gami da bat, civet, linzamin kwamfuta da kare raccoon, wanda ke ba da damar watsa kwayar cutar tsakanin jinsuna.
A zahiri, an lura da ragowar amino acid 6 kawai sun bambanta da na mutum da na kwayar cutar kwayar cutar a cikin RBD kuma 4 daga cikinsu suna cikin yanayin da ke ɗaure mai karɓar don hulɗa tare da mai karɓar ACE2.
Civet SARS-CoV yana da sauye-sauyen K479N da S487T a cikin RBD, wanda zai iya haɓaka kusanci na hulɗar furotin mai ƙwanƙwasa tare da mai karɓar ACE2 na ɗan adam.
A wasu kalmomi, waɗannan maye gurbin amino acid guda biyu na iya zama mahimmanci ga daidaitawar kwayar cutar ga mutane.
Ya kamata a lura cewa SARS-CoV-2 yana da mai karɓar kwayar halitta iri ɗaya tare da SARS-CoV.
Bambanci na 30% tsakanin SARS-CoV-2 da SARS-CoV a cikin S1 na furotin S yana nuna cewa alaƙar da ke haɗa furotin S tare da ACE2 na ɗan adam na iya canzawa.
Tabbas, binciken cryo-EM ya nuna kusancin wannan haɗin sau 10 zuwa 20 fiye da na tsakanin ACE2 na ɗan adam da furotin SARS-CoV S.
Hakanan zai zama mai ban sha'awa don sanin ko ana iya buƙatar kowane mai karɓar ƙwayar cuta don watsa SARS-CoV-2.
Abin sha'awa, HCoV-NL63 shima yana ɗaure zuwa ACE2 amma tare da wani ɓangare na S.
